    <h1>h1: Example Page Heading</h1>
    <p class="lead text-muted">This is an example of applying the "lead" and "text-muted" paragraph classes.</p>
    <p>And this is an example of a normal paragraph. You can find this example page in the source code at <strong>app/views/static_pages/example.html.erb</strong>. Here's an example of a link within a paragraph: <a href="https://google.com">Google</a>. Links get an underline when they're part of a paragraph or part of a definition list's description, but otherwise don't get an underline (like in the list below).</p>
    <h2>h2: Common Internal Links</h2>
    <p>Here's a list of common internal links in the Rails template language:</p>
    <ul class="list-unstyled">
      <li><%= link_to 'Home', root_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'About OAC', about_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'Contributing Institutions', { controller: 'arclight/repositories', action: 'index' } %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'FAQs', help_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'Link with a forced underline', help_path, class: 'link-underline' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'Terms of Use', termsofuse_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'Privacy Statement', privacy_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'Accessibility', 'https://cdlib.org/about/policies-and-guidelines/accessibility/' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'Contact Us', contact_form_path, data: {turbo: "false"} %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'About the Collection Guides in OAC', overview_path %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'CDL Privacy Statement', 'https://cdlib.org/about/policies-and-guidelines/privacy-statement/' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'California Digital Library', 'https://cdlib.org/' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to 'University of California Libraries', 'https://libraries.universityofcalifornia.edu/' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "View Collection Guide", solr_document_path("ark:/13030/c8xg9zfj") %></li>
